This place showed the worst service I have ever seen.  I have ordered chicked gyros where the meat was undentifiable substance . After I have asked the waiter his answer was : it is imitation of the lamb meat. When he saw we didn’t eat our food he brought us cheesecake what was a nice gesture if the cake wouldn’t be frozen. In the end we asked for the bill where he added his own gratuity 6$ for the horrible service and he wasn’t willing to take it off. Horrible quality food with even worse service.

I wish I could have tasted the food, but the diner failed horribly on that part. I ordered my food at 9:27am via Pearl Diner’s direct website (pearl dinernyc.com) and received an email from Food.io with my order number. Good thing that I contacted the restaurant as I wanted to make sure they received the side note about how to make my eggs. When the employee answered, he states that my order isn’t there. He asked if I’m sure I placed it at that location and I told him yes and this is the number associated with my order. He states he will look for it and calls me back within 5 minutes. He informs me that a couple orders came in and mine hadn’t. He will reach out to confirm my order. Well, he never calls back, but I call about 15 minutes later. He proceeds to inform me that the order isn’t there and he called GrubHub and they don’t have it. I told him that it wasn’t placed through GrubHub and my email confirmation came from Food.io. He proceeds to tell me that GrubHub didn’t have the order and I repeatedly stated that it didn’t go through GrubHub.  Another callback was made and a manager requested. In a nutshell, the manager states he cannot do anything about it since it was done through Food.io. While I understand that that was the delivery service, the order itself was placed through Pearl Diner’s website. The manager didn’t even want to give me the phone number to Food.io even though he couldn’t do anything about it. He referred me online and was absolutely no assistance.  I work in Customer Service and this was a HORRIBLE first impression for me. I will never eat there (again never got to try the food anyway) and any chance I get, I’ll speak of this experience. There was ZERO effort to assist the consumer. If the manager had shown a little empathy (oh and by the way, my card was charged too) and attempted to contact Food.io (your employee was able to contact GrubHub, but not Food.io) to figure out the issue, this review would be a little more pleasant because at least, someone tried. He stated Food.io is open on weekends, but here now after 15 calls thus far, I’m still getting a voicemail.  Again, one of the worst experiences!
